From: Paul Fulghum <paulkf@microgate.com>
> You need to get pppd to either authenticate the peer (NT) with
> chap-m$soft (I'm not sure how, look at the docs) or disable
> authentication of the peer (noauth option).
To follow up my own post, MS-CHAP is only supported for the
linux client, not for linux to authenticate others. So the choice is
to use PAP to authenticate NT or noauth.
